Issue:
 'SSH failed attempts alerts' not visible in Wazuh dashboard.

Root Cause:
 Kali Linux used journald only for logging, (/var/log/auth.log) must exist before Wazuh can monitor it. 
 (/var/log/auth.log) was missing missing in ossec.conf file.

Fix:
- Added this block to ossec.config at the end of file just before '</ossec_config>':

 ```bash
 <localfile>
    <log_format>syslog</log_format>
    <location>/var/log/auth.log</location>
  </localfile>
 ```
- Installed rsyslog (it writes SSH failures to /var/log/auth.log)
- Removed dashboard 'authentication_success' filter.

Result:
SSH brute-force alerts detected successfully.
